<p>
<em class="u">NOTE¹:</em> The <code>-e</code> option of the <code>echo</code> command enable the parsing of the escape sequences.
</p>

<p>
<em class="u">NOTE²:</em> The “<code>\e[0m</code>” sequence removes all attributes (formatting and colors). It can be a good idea to add it at the end of each colored text. ;) 
</p>

<p>
<em class="u">NOTE³:</em> The examples in this page are in <strong>Bash</strong> but the <strong>ANSI/VT100</strong> escape sequences can be used in every programming languages.
</p>

</div>

